// place-barracks.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A barracks / guardhouse — the town's armed force at home. A working
// site, not a shop: commander, the unit and its strength, readiness
// and morale, what they're currently dealing with, and a hook.
//
// Entry table: [@TF-Barracks]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// Reuses people.ipt. No prices.

Title: Barracks
Use: people.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} barracks
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Barracks
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: cmdr=[@PersonName]
Set: canc=[@Ancestry]
**[@BarracksTitle]** *(barracks in {$town})*\n&
**[@BarracksType], [@BarracksCondition]**\n&
**Commander:** [@CommanderRank] {$cmdr}, a [@PersonDesc] {$canc} who is [@CommanderStyle].\n&
**The unit:** [@Unit]\n&
**Readiness:** [@Readiness]\n&
**On duty now:** [@BarracksActivity]\n&
**Trouble brewing:** [@BarracksHook]

Table: BarracksTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@BarracksName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: BarracksName
The [@BarracksNameWord] Barracks
[@BarracksNameWord] Guardhouse
The [@BarracksNameWord] Watch-house

Table: BarracksNameWord
Old
North
Gate
River
High
Garrison
Wall
Iron

Table: BarracksType
The seat of the town watch
A garrison of the local lord's soldiers
A militia muster-hall, half its racks empty between call-ups
A mercenary company's rented quarters
A border fort's barracks, hard-used and serious
A small guardhouse with cells and a duty-desk

Table: BarracksCondition
well-drilled and orderly
stretched thin and short-handed
freshly reinforced after recent trouble
slack and comfortable in a quiet posting
tense, on alert for something unspecified
demoralised, with pay weeks overdue

Table: CommanderRank
Captain
Sergeant
Watch-Commander
Lieutenant
Sergeant-at-Arms
Marshal

Table: CommanderStyle
fair, sharp, and respected by the ranks
a martinet who drills the watch to exhaustion
competent but cynical after too many years
ambitious, treating the post as a stepping stone
genuinely brave and loved, if a poor administrator
corrupt in small, deniable ways
new to command and overcompensating

Table: Unit
{!n=={8+2d10}}roughly {$n} {!sg==[@SoldierType]}{$sg}, [@UnitTrait]

Table: SoldierType
town guards
militia volunteers
seasoned soldiers
green recruits
mercenaries on contract
mounted patrol-riders

Table: UnitTrait
loyal to the commander before the town
more interested in dice than drills
recently bloodied and a little jumpy
well-equipped but poorly led
locals who know every face in town
outsiders the townsfolk don't fully trust

Table: Readiness
arms racked and ready, a patrol out at all hours
nominally on watch, in practice half-asleep
on high alert — leave is cancelled
under-equipped; the armoury is suspiciously bare
drilling hard for something the commander won't name
stood down, with most of the unit off-duty in the taverns

Table: BarracksActivity
a prisoner is being questioned in a back room, not gently
new recruits are being put through their paces in the yard
the duty officer is buried in paperwork and bad temper
a patrol just came in with someone in irons
dice and complaints around the guardroom stove
an inspection has everyone scrubbing and polishing
the watch is mustering for something, fast and quiet

Table: BarracksHook
weapons have gone missing from the armoury and it's being hushed up
the commander is quietly recruiting outsiders for an off-the-books job
a prisoner in the cells is not who the charge-sheet says they are
half the unit's loyalty has been bought; the commander suspects but can't prove it
patrols keep being sent away from one particular district
a soldier deserted last night, taking something they shouldn't have
the watch has been ordered to ignore a crime everyone can see
pay-chests arrived light, and someone in the chain is skimming

// Standalone name roll (collision-proof, for note titles etc.).
Table: TF-BarracksName
[@BarracksName]
